From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: AWS Account Team <noreply@amazon.com>
Date: Fri, 1 May 2026 03:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix bench_serving sglang-oai streaming chunk parser

The OpenAI /v1/completions streaming parser in
async_request_openai_completions has three latent bugs that surface when
benchmarking sglang 0.5.10 with --backend sglang-oai:

1. `data["choices"][0]` IndexError on usage-only chunks.
   sglang (and vLLM with include_usage=true) emits a trailing
   {"choices": [], "usage": {...}} chunk to report final token counts.
   The current code does data["choices"][0]["text"] unconditionally,
   which raises IndexError → the request is marked failed. sglang-oai-chat
   does not hit this because the chat parser checks choices truthiness
   before indexing. Fix: guard with `if data.get("choices")`.

2. `choices[0]["text"]` may be None (not "") on some reasoning-content
   paths. `None` still fails the truthiness test so no crash, but it
   silently drops the text chunk. Guard with `text or ""`.

3. TTFT chunk text was never appended to output.text_chunks (only the
   decode-phase chunks are). generated_text catches it via +=, but any
   consumer that iterates text_chunks (e.g. per-chunk latency analysis)
   misses the first token. Move the append out of the else branch so
   both TTFT and decode chunks are recorded.

Upstream-ref: observed on sglang==0.5.10 bench_serving.py
              async_request_openai_completions around L275-L318.
---
 sglang/bench_serving.py | 24 +++++++++++++-----------
 1 file changed, 13 insertions(+), 11 deletions(-)

diff --git a/sglang/bench_serving.py b/sglang/bench_serving.py
index 0000000..1111111 100644
--- a/sglang/bench_serving.py
+++ b/sglang/bench_serving.py
@@ -297,22 +297,24 @@ async def async_request_openai_completions(
                         else:
                             data = json.loads(chunk)

-                            # NOTE: Some completion API might have a last
-                            # usage summary response without a token so we
-                            # want to check a token was generated
-                            if data["choices"][0]["text"]:
+                            # usage-only chunks (choices==[] with usage) must
+                            # not index [0]; text may be None on reasoning
+                            # paths; treat both as "no token this chunk".
+                            choices = data.get("choices") or []
+                            text = (choices[0].get("text") if choices else None) or ""
+                            if text:
                                 timestamp = time.perf_counter()
                                 # First token
                                 if ttft == 0.0:
                                     ttft = time.perf_counter() - st
                                     output.ttft = ttft
-
-                                # Decoding phase
+                                # Decoding phase — record ITL only (first
+                                # token's latency is TTFT, not an ITL).
                                 else:
-                                    output.text_chunks.append(
-                                        data["choices"][0]["text"]
-                                    )
                                     output.itl.append(timestamp - most_recent_timestamp)

+                                # Both TTFT and decode chunks contribute to
+                                # text_chunks (bug: original only appended
+                                # in the decode branch, dropping first token).
+                                output.text_chunks.append(text)
                                 most_recent_timestamp = timestamp
-                                generated_text += data["choices"][0]["text"]
+                                generated_text += text
                                 output_len = (data.get("usage") or {}).get(
                                     "completion_tokens", output_len
                                 )
--
